Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.75,0:01:00.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙中有数十亿颗恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are billions of stars in the Universe
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.51,0:01:03.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但只有一颗宇宙近邻主宰着我们:\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but one alone dominates our cosmic neighborhood:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.72,0:01:05.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.44,0:01:10.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是一颗地狱般的星球 大部分是氢和氦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's an infernal sphere, of mostly hydrogen and helium,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.60,0:01:14.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,高温成为等离子体 在数百万度下燃烧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}superheated into a plasma, that burns at millions of degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.32,0:01:18.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其表面猛烈地爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Its surface reages with violent explosions,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.35,0:01:23.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,抛出致命的辐射风暴进入数百万英哩的太空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as it spews out storms of deadly radiation, millions of miles into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.25,0:01:27.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的太阳是称做黄矮星一类的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our Sun is a type of star known as a yellow dwarf.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.61,0:01:30.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黄是因为其表面的颜色\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Yellow because of the colour of its surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.31,0:01:34.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而矮是因为它是一颗小恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and dwarf because it's small for a star.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.26,0:01:35.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但小是相对的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But small is relative.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.27,0:01:39.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在它的边界范围内可以放进一百万个地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Within its boundaries, you could fit one million earths.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.04,0:01:48.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在我们的太阳系根本没有比太阳更大的星体了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In our Solar System, there's simply no bigger star than the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.08,0:01:53.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在数百万英哩范围内 它是巨大的天体炸弹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At a million miles across, it's a massive celestial blockbuster.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.40,0:01:56.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳实在是相当巨大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun is really pretty huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.67,0:01:58.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它支配着我们的太阳系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It dominates our Solar System.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.71,0:02:01.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不仅是太阳系里最大的星体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Not only is the bigger star of the Solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.62,0:02:03.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且是太阳系里唯一的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's the only star in the Solar System.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.91,0:02:05.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的四周围绕着较小的物体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's sorrounded by a bunch a smaller stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.74,0:02:07.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们称之为行星 慧星和卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we call planets and comets and moons.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.93,0:02:10.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而太阳是我们的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the Sun is our star.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.58,0:02:16.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的恒星是热和能源巨大的来源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our star is an enormous source of heat and energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.67,0:02:21.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有10000华氏度(约5560摄氏度)的表面温度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It has a surface temperature of 10,000 Farenheit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.43,0:02:26.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生3 8万亿亿兆瓦特的能源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And generates 380 billion billion megawatts of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.10,0:02:30.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人类在此显得微不足道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This dwarfs anything on the human scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.38,0:02:35.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,内华达州的胡佛水坝仅发电280兆瓦特\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hoover Dam in Nevada only generates 280 megawatts.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.25,0:02:41.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳一秒钟制造的能源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In one second the Sun churns out more energy
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.71,0:02:45.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比所有人类文明社会用过的能源还要多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than has been used in all of human civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.96,0:02:48.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所有的能量在眨眼之间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All that power in the blink of an eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.69,0:02:54.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,无法相信的是太阳已经以这种方式燃烧了数十亿年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Incredibly, it's been burning this way for billions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.99,0:02:59.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,早期的科学家没有搞明白\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Early astronomers didn't quite understand how
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.04,0:03:02.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳为什么能够在这么长的时期内产生如此多的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Sun could generate so much energy for that long a period of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.36,0:03:07.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真正的第一个谜是太阳怎样产生能量的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That was the first mistery, it was really how the Sun generates its energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.05,0:03:10.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在19世纪早期\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the early nineteenth century,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.84,0:03:14.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家假设太阳就像地球上的火\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}scientists assumed that the Sun worked just like any fire on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.94,0:03:19.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来自像煤这样的燃料慢慢地燃烧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that there was a source of fuel, perhaps coal, that was slowly burning away.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.21,0:03:22.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而这个理论的一个严重的问题:\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But that was a serious problem with this theory:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.42,0:03:24.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我的面前有一堆火\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I've got a fire in front of me here,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.68,0:03:27.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果我想维持燃烧 就要不停地给加入木头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if I want it to keep burning, I have to keep adding wood to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.31,0:03:30.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这火大概只能维持一个小时 除非加进更多的木头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This fire will last maybe an hour, unless I add some more wood.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.71,0:03:33.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在假如我有像太阳那样大的一堆木头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, if I had a pile of the wood the size of the whole Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.31,0:03:35.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同时某种程度上有足够的氧气来燃烧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and somehow enough oxygen to burn it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.07,0:03:38.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只能维持大约5000到6000年的燃烧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would only take about 5000 or 6000 years to burn out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.00,0:03:43.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是一个长的时间 但还不够长得足够支撑地球的生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's a long time, but it's not long enough to sustain life on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.26,0:03:46.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在20世纪早期\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By the early twentieth century,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.98,0:03:50.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球岩石和化石的碳-14年代测定证实\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}carbon dating of Earth rocks and fossils had proven
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.09,0:03:54.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳已经以足够维持生命的温度存在了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the Sun was in existence and at temperatures warm enough to sustain life
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.71,0:03:58.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不是几千年而是30亿年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}not for thousands of years, but for 3 billion.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.06,0:04:02.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你想烧一把维持这么长时间的火\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you wanted to build a fire that would last that long,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.23,0:04:05.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你就需要72万亿捆的柴火\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you would need 72 trillion cords of firewood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.07,0:04:10.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是地球上每一个男人 女人和孩子各12000捆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's 12,000 cords for each man, woman and child on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.64,0:04:14.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,显然必须有其它的一些作业方式\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Clearly, there had to be some other process,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.99,0:04:18.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是地球上未知的动力 供应着太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}unknow on Earth, that was powering the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.82,0:04:22.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,1929年科学家在掌握氢弹核燃料后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the 1920's scientists found the answer to the puzzle,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.56,0:04:26.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,找到了谜题的答案\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in a process that would later be harnessed to fuel the hydrogen bomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.86,0:04:28.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,核聚变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Nuclear fusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.80,0:04:33.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,聚变发生在原子被高速打碎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Fusion occurs when atoms are smashed together at a high rate of speed
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.54,0:04:36.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并逐个重组聚合 为了达到目的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and literally fused. To get this to happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.45,0:04:38.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,条件都必须恰到好处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}conditions have to be just right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.18,0:04:42.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这发生了一些相互作用--两个质子 每个质子各带\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For any interaction to happen, these two protons, each has
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.57,0:04:46.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个正电荷 因此相互排斥\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a positive electric charge and so they would repell each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.63,0:04:48.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你想让它们充分靠近\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so you got to get them close enough together.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.36,0:04:51.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要做到这一点则需要加热 这意味着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And to do that, it's got to be hot, which means
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.49,0:04:55.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,粒子运动速度加快 足够密集 彼此撞击和\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the particles are moving fast, and dense enough that they, they hit each other
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.03,0:04:58.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相互足够地靠近而实现聚合\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they can get close enough together so they actually fuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.00,0:05:02.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳的核心是个完美的核聚变反应堆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The core of the Sun is the perfect cauldron for nuclear fusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.17,0:05:08.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是太阳系中最热的地方 有2700万华氏度(1500万摄氏度)\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's the hottest place in the Solar System, at a sweltering 27 milion Degrees Fahrenheit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.89,0:05:10.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且它也非常的密集\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it's also incredibly dense.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.38,0:05:14.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是如此的密 其密度是铅的10倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's so dense, it's ten times the density of lead,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.04,0:05:18.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你会认为那么高的密度会是一个固体 但不是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you would think at that density it should be a solid, but it's not
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.09,0:05:20.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而是高热状态下等离子体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because it's so hot that remains a plasma.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.25,0:05:23.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你把气体加热到足够的高温\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you heat a gas to high enough temperatures
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.94,0:05:26.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,电子脱离了原子 像漂浮在汤里的漂浮物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}electrons fall off of the atoms and they float around in the soup.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.24,0:05:32.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此它有着不同于气体的性质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so it has behavior that's different from what a gas would do,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.40,0:05:35.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们有一个不同的名字来描述叫做等离子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hence we have a different word for it, we call it plasma.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.21,0:05:40.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要真正明白太阳核里进行着什么\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To truly understand what goes on in the core of the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.42,0:05:44.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你必须以某种方式去想像 简直是"不可思议"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you have to find some way to imagine the almost "unimaginable"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.38,0:05:49.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,除了研究太阳以外我还玩撞球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In addition to studying the Sun, I also play pool
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.38,0:05:55.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳中有着无数粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the Sun is a place where there are billions of particles,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.28,0:05:57.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相互冲撞 作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}colliding and interacting with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.03,0:06:05.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在一个不可思议的规模内 它和宇宙撞球桌没什麽区别\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it is really not unlike a cosmic pool table, on an unimaginable scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.09,0:06:09.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很难打中一个球 这无所谓\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It doesn't matter how hard you hit a ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.19,0:06:12.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上那个球击中另一个聚合在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You would never hit hard enough to actually
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.01,0:06:14.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不会很困难\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}fuse that ball together with another ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.61,0:06:19.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而在有如此高的压力 密度的太阳核里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But there's so much pressure and such high density at the core of the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.88,0:06:24.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两个物体可轻易地相互碰撞 融合在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that two objects impacting each other, will actually fuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.63,0:06:29.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在太阳里这些物体是氢原子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the Sun, these objects are hydrogen atoms,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.72,0:06:33.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在巨大的压力下飞撞在一起 形成氦原子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}flung together by immense pressure, to form helium atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.11,0:06:38.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这个聚合过程中 产生的原子(氦)比初始原子(等离子氢)的质量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In this fusion process, the resulting atom is slightly less massive
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.12,0:06:39.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,稍微小一点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than the ones they created it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.09,0:06:42.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,缺少的质量作为能源释放了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The missing mass is given off as energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.62,0:06:49.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每一秒钟太阳内部有6亿吨氢聚合\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Each second, inside the Sun, 600 million tons of hydrogen are fused
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.51,0:06:52.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生5 95亿吨氦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into 595 million tons of helium.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.91,0:06:57.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,缺失的500万吨质量转换成了能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That five million tons of mass lost in the process is converted into energy
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.57,0:07:01.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等于10亿个百万吨级的氢弹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}equal to one billion one megaton hydrogen bombs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.49,0:07:03.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是在每一秒内\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's every second.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.83,0:07:05.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当你注意到宇宙间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When you look out into the cosmos,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.75,0:07:08.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,获得免费的能源最大的收益的途径\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the process that gives you the highest return of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.87,0:07:12.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在于像太阳那样的恒星中心进行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for free, is what goes on in the centers of stars like the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.87,0:07:15.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在我们知道了太阳是靠核聚变产生能量的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, we now know that the Sun is powered by nuclear fusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.52,0:07:17.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是我们知道的唯一燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's the only fuel we know,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.49,0:07:20.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能够承担太阳燃烧长期提供能源支撑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that can sustain the burning in the Sun long enough
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.80,0:07:23.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球的生命达数十亿年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to sustain life on Earth, billions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.20,0:07:26.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阳光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.58,0:07:32.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对生活是如此的重要 我们一秒钟都无法离开它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's so central to life that we don't often give it a second thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.31,0:07:40.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而光从那里到这里原来是个难以置信的故事\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But how light gets from there to here, turns out to be an incredible story.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.43,0:07:46.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,聚变产生的能量送出太阳的核心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The energy created in the fusion process is carried out of the core
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.72,0:07:49.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是靠光和热的粒子叫做光子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by particles of light and heat called photons.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.55,0:07:54.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,光子把太阳的温暖带给地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are what bring the warming rays of the Sun to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.48,0:07:58.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为了来到我们地球 这些来自我们最近的恒星的光子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To reach our planet, these glowing travellers from our nearest star
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.87,0:08:02.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,必须首先经过太阳各层 漫长艰辛的道路\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}must first take a long winding road through all the layers of the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.02,0:08:05.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像但丁到地狱各层去一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like Dante journeying through the levels of Hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.28,0:08:11.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,首先光子进入185000英哩长的辐射区\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}First, a photon enters the 185,000 mile-thick radiative zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.45,0:08:13.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,区内的道路是如此的崎岖\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The region is so densely packed
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.12,0:08:15.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,光子经常游荡进入其它粒子里面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the photon constantly bumps into other particles,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.12,0:08:17.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如氢和氦原子里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like hydrogen and helium atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.34,0:08:20.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它以无序曲折的模式向外挣扎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It struggles outward in a chaotic zigzag
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.82,0:08:24.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种模式科学家称之为"随机游动"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}pattern that scientists call the "random walk"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.37,0:08:28.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,光子如果没有一而再 再而三的相互作用是无法逃逸的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A photon can't escape without interacting over and over and over again,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.01,0:08:31.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它被原子吸收和重新接纳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}getting absorbed by atoms and reemitted
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.97,0:08:34.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能够被吸收和重新接纳数百万次\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it can be absorbed and reemitted millions of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.46,0:08:45.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着密度减小光子可以更远地离开太阳中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the density decreases as you get further up in the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.97,0:08:49.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,变得较为宽松 相互作用减少\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it becomes easier and the collisions and the interactions are less.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.29,0:08:55.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当到达距离太阳表面130000英哩时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When it finally reaches to within 130,000 miles of the surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.93,0:08:58.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,光子进入了对流层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the photon enters the convective zone,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.70,0:09:00.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,速度突然加快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the pace suddenly quickens.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.14,0:09:03.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被一种沸腾卷的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's carried upwards by a kind of boiling,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.00,0:09:08.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,巨大的气柱裹着 以每小时几百英哩卷出去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}riding along in huge columns of gas at hundreds of miles an hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.82,0:09:12.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到达太阳表面只要10天功夫\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}taking only ten days to emerge on the solar surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.48,0:09:17.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着光子通过太阳稀薄的大气层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The incredible journey is almost over
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.77,0:09:22.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,难以置信的旅程差不多就结束了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as the photon lifts off through the wispy gasses of the solar atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.24,0:09:25.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从那只须8分钟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From there, it takes only 8 minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.43,0:09:29.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,穿过9300万英哩的空间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for it to zip across 93 million miles of space
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.48,0:09:30.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到达我们地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.14,0:09:36.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,无法相信在阳光真正到达地球时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Incredibly, by the time sunlight actually reaches Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.80,0:09:38.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,光子已经存在了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's already been in existence
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.59,0:09:42.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成千上万年 甚至百万年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for hundreds of thousands, if not millions, of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.33,0:09:58.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对太阳来说百万年实在是微不足道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For the Sun even a million years is a small blip in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.79,0:10:01.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,完美的日落\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The simple perfect disc of a sunset,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.31,0:10:04.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,掩饰着我们的恒星长期狂暴的历史\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}belies the long, violent history of our star.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.04,0:10:09.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是诞生在数十亿年前的火球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is a ball of fire spawned billions of years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.06,0:10:12.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生在一次被认为是超新星的巨大爆发里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in a massive explosion known as a supernova.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.09,0:10:18.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在那次大爆发后那颗远比太阳大的恒星破碎了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}After this titanic explosion where a star much larger than the Sun exploded,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.57,0:10:23.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,留下了比太阳系大许多倍 巨大的气体云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there would have been a huge cloud of gas many times larger than the Solar System.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.27,0:10:28.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这个非常巨大的云里 崩塌的小碎片\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And small nods of material would have gradually coalesced
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.00,0:10:29.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,逐渐地合并\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in this very large cloud.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.00,0:10:31.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大约50亿年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}About five billion years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.93,0:10:34.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大爆炸后大约100亿年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}some ten billion years after the Big Bang
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.43,0:10:37.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家认为我们的宇宙坍缩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that scientists believe kickstarted our Universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.36,0:10:40.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在万有引力作用下开始坍缩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}this cloud started to collapse under the pull of gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.96,0:10:44.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的太阳系可能产生于这样一个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our Solar System probably arose from one such nod
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.00,0:10:47.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,气体相互牵引自由结合的碎片\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of self gravitating gas that pulled itself together
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.65,0:10:49.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,逐渐自己环绕着转起来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and gradually spun itself up
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.75,0:10:53.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它收缩起来就像溜冰者在自旋时收起双臂一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as it pulled in, like a skater pulling her arms in during a spin,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.70,0:10:57.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直到太阳形成和各种行星收缩围绕着它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}until the star and the various planets coalesced around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.06,0:11:01.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最后当太阳足够致密 开始\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ultimately, when the star was dense enough, it would have turned on
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.92,0:11:04.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,氢聚变点火 开始发热发光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}fusion, started glowing and giving off sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.19,0:11:10.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为什么科学家认为太阳是从超新星的灰烬里诞生的呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why do scientists believe the Sun was born from the ashes of a supernova?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.01,0:11:13.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这明显地在我们脚下展现出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The evidence lies beneath our feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.67,0:11:15.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,复杂的重元素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Complex heavy elements
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.19,0:11:19.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如我们从地球上开采出来用于发电厂的燃料的铀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like the uranium we mine from the Earth to fuel our nuclear powerplants,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.35,0:11:21.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是无法在太阳上制造出来的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could not have been forged in the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.61,0:11:24.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳那样大小的恒星没有足够的热量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there is simply not enough heat in a star of that size
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.63,0:11:27.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,去产生任何比铁重的元素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to create elements any heavier than iron.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.75,0:11:30.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,重元素--像铀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Heavy elements, like uranium,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.38,0:11:34.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只能产生在灾难性的宇宙爆炸中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can only be created in a catastrophic cosmic explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.70,0:11:39.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在太阳系里地球和其它行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth and the other planets in the Solar System
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.43,0:11:42.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,的形成 不同于构成太阳的气体物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}formed out of the same nod of gas that produced the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.34,0:11:47.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这里太阳占有了99%的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In this process the Sun hoarded 99% of the mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.71,0:11:51.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就意味着它是宇宙中我们邻近的最大的物体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This means it's the biggest object in our celestial neighborhood,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.24,0:11:53.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有最强的引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with the strongest gravitational pull.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.97,0:11:56.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是其它物体围绕着它旋转的原因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's why everything else revolves around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.53,0:12:02.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相对于其它行星地球争得了对于太阳的特殊位置\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Of all the planets, Earth earned a privileged place in relation to the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.54,0:12:04.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果太靠近太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If we were closer in,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.80,0:12:09.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大海将沸腾蒸发 地面会热得足以把铅融化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our oceans would boil away and the ground would be hot enough to melt lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.44,0:12:13.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果太远我们的星球将变成冰冻的废墟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If we were farther out, our planet would be a frozen wasteland.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.41,0:12:16.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以就像Goldylocks和三头熊\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a sort of like Goldylocks and the Three Bears,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.65,0:12:19.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不太热也不太冷 正好\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}not too hot, not too cold, it's just right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.97,0:12:22.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里大约距离太阳9300万英哩远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here we are at about 93 million miles away
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.91,0:12:26.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能在这里我们幸福 幸运\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the Sun and we're happy to be here, we're lucky to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.80,0:12:30.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,感觉上说我们这的环境不错\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In some sense we're here because it's the right circumstance for us to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.44,0:12:35.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球是太阳系里刚刚正好的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth may be in just the right place in the Solar System,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.11,0:12:40.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但也有缺陷 容易成为太阳发怒的靶子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but we're also close enough to the Sun to be a target of its fury.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.03,0:12:47.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每年数以千计的爆发晃动着我们的太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thousands of mammoth explosions rock our Sun every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.30,0:12:56.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你可能认为这种爆发来自太阳中心的核反应\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You might expect this explosive force to come from nuclear reactions in the core,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.56,0:13:03.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上驱使太阳猛烈爆发的是磁力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but in reality what drives all outbursts of solar violence is magnetism.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.38,0:13:07.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,自从太阳像固体那样自转后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Since Earth rotates as a solid,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.70,0:13:12.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的磁场就很简单 有两个磁极--北极和南极\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our magnetic field is simple, we have two poles: North and South.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.72,0:13:16.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是罗盘能在地球上指示方向的原因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is what makes a compass so useful for finding your way around the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.54,0:13:22.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是想像一下每100-1000万年两极替换\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But imagine if instead of two poles you had 1 to 10 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.82,0:13:24.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是太阳引起的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is what happens on the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.15,0:13:27.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳的磁场\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun's magnetic field
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.78,0:13:31.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是靠引力结合在一起的一张复杂的网\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a tangled web because even though it's held together by gravity,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.09,0:13:34.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等离子无法均匀的旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the plasma doesn't rotate evenly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.83,0:13:36.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等离子在赤道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Plasma at the equator
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.20,0:13:38.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,旋转一圈平均为25个地球日\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}rotates once every 25 Earth days,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.83,0:13:43.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而在两极旋转一圈就需要35天\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}while plasma at the poles takes roughly 35 days to circle once.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.61,0:13:46.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳被我们称为差动自转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun has what we call differential rotation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.30,0:13:49.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所有的等离子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You have all this plasma
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.20,0:13:51.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它旋转啊旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that is really turning and turning
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.31,0:13:54.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,造成磁场扭曲\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that causes magnetic field lines to become twisted
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.94,0:13:57.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,内部纠缠在一块\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and intertwined and mixed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.72,0:14:01.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管看不见磁力线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Although magnetic field lines are invisible,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.46,0:14:03.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但我们知道它存在于太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we know they exist on the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.07,0:14:06.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其特征被称为"冕环"和"日珥"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by looking at features called "coronal loops" and "prominences"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.11,0:14:09.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一路上升到太阳大气层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}rising up into the solar atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.76,0:14:17.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像金属屑排列在一个简单磁场里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just as metal shavings line up in the presence of a simple magnet,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.49,0:14:19.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些等离子的回路\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}these loops of plasma
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.01,0:14:22.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从下面完美地描绘了支持它们的磁构造\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}perfectly outline the magnetic structures that support them from below.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.98,0:14:27.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些等离子拱桥是如此的高和宽大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These plasma arches are so tall and wide
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.12,0:14:30.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以把木星那样大的行星放进去穿过它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that you could slide a planet as big as Jupiter right through them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.43,0:14:34.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有时磁场会扭曲在太阳大气中的等离子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sometimes magnetic fields can twist plasma
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.16,0:14:38.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,进入称为"通量绳"的宏伟的螺旋体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the Sun's atmosphere into majestic helical shapes called "flux ropes"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.08,0:14:41.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磁场通量绳有点苗条\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A magnetic flux rope is sort of like a slinky.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.69,0:14:44.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磁力线被包裹在螺旋结构里许多次\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The magnetic field line is wrapped around many times in a helical structure,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.12,0:14:48.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一旦有了高度盘旋的磁力线后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and when you have highly twisted magnetic field lines,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.73,0:14:52.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就储存了大量的磁能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it carries a lot of stored free magnetic energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.08,0:14:54.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有时甚至会自己缠绕在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and sometimes it will even kink in on itself
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.47,0:14:57.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还能储存更多的磁能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which gives it even more stored magnetic free energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.99,0:15:02.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些等离子红焰能持续几个星期或几个月\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These plasma prominencies can last for weeks or months,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.04,0:15:05.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是最后储存的能量会释放\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but eventually the stored up energy has to be released,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.32,0:15:07.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,质量会飞入太空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the mass is flung off into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.31,0:15:20.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在太阳磁场最盘根错节的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Where the Sun's magnetic field is at its most twisted and complex,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.59,0:15:23.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,保持着底下上来的热涌动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}heat bubbling up from below is kept
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.14,0:15:26.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,物质的温度要低1000度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the material is cooled by as much as 1000 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.35,0:15:30.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,结果形成了黑斑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What results are relatively dark blemishes
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.25,0:15:33.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在太阳表面称为"黑子".\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the solar surface called "sunspots"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.40,0:15:38.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑子的暗只不过是对应着周围明亮的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sunspots are only dark in relation to the bright material around them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.91,0:15:42.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你能将其中一个放到空中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you could somehow suspend one alone up in space,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.43,0:15:45.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它会比满月亮10倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would shine 10 times brighter than the full Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.90,0:15:50.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些明显的小斑点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These apparently tiny blemishes
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.97,0:15:55.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上是等离子创造出来的 相当于整个地球大小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are actually plasma craters the size of the entire Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.17,0:16:00.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伽利略是现代第一个观察太阳黑子的科学家\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Galileo was one the first modern scientists to observe sunspots.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.06,0:16:05.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他使用望远镜把太阳的影像投射到纸上并描绘出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Using a telescope he projected an image of the Sun onto paper and traced it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.52,0:16:10.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他看到了斑点越过太阳表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He realized that the blemishes were moving across the face of the star,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.40,0:16:13.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,第一次指出太阳的旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which was the first indication that the Sun rotated.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.21,0:16:17.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不仅太阳在旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Not only does the Sun rotate,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.18,0:16:21.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且一些黑子自身也会在太阳表面旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but sunspots themselves can actually spin like hurricanes on the solar surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.59,0:16:26.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,此时黑子的磁力线变得非常的扭曲\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And when they do, their magnetic field lines become extremely twisted.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.28,0:16:31.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,扭曲的磁力线意味着更多的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Twisted magnetic field lines mean more energy
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.40,0:16:34.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而更多的能量意味着潜在的大爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and more energy means the potential for huge eruptions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.11,0:16:38.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想像下橡皮条就像磁力线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Think of a rubber band as magnetic field line.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.05,0:16:43.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你扭曲它 充分扭曲它 它就得到了所有的能量；\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you twist it, and you twist enough it's goin to have all that energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.81,0:16:45.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而当你放开它时 能量就释放出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and when you let it go it's going to release.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.61,0:16:52.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你拆掉橡皮条就不会飞行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you just take an untwisted rubber band and release it it's not going to fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.63,0:17:00.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当太阳黑子释放其磁能时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When a sunspot unleashes its magnetic energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.81,0:17:04.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就会在太阳系引发最激烈的爆发:\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what results are the most colossal explosions in the Solar System:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.08,0:17:06.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳耀斑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}solar flares.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.33,0:17:11.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,单个耀斑会释放10亿兆顿当量的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A single flare releases as much as a billion megatons of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.22,0:17:16.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等于地球上一百万座火山喷发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The combined power of a million volcanic eruptions on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.69,0:17:19.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们看来是非常\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They appear as these very
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.11,0:17:23.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,白色的区域是如此的明亮 这是因为其温度是如此的高\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}bright regions and they're so bright because the temperature is so high,
