Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.20,0:27:18.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许相当于100次X光胸透\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}perhaps are those equal to a hundred chest x-rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.33,0:27:22.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这不是我们想要管的乱七八糟的事 因为永远不知道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's not something that we want to mess around with, because we never know
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.61,0:27:24.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当那辐射可能突然变得\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when that radiation might all of a sudden become
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.83,0:27:28.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,更加激烈 而此时天上正好有飞机飞行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a lot more intense while there's an airplane in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.43,0:27:31.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来自太阳辐射的威胁只是多了一个理由\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The threat from solar radiation is just one more reason
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.85,0:27:34.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让科学家密切关注太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for scientists to keep a close watch on our Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.99,0:27:38.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳的活动特别是在当代 事关紧要\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It matters, especially in modern times, what the Sun is doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.48,0:27:39.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球不是安全岛\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth is not an island.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.14,0:27:43.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们是太阳系活动的参与者\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We are participant in the activities of the Solar System.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.11,0:27:47.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳黑子会引发更剧烈的太阳风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sunspots are the triggers for more severe solar storms,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.93,0:27:50.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以预报员小心地跟踪它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so forecasters track them carefully,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.48,0:27:53.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在它们越过太阳表面时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as they rotate across the surface of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.68,0:27:59.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地点 地点 地点 我们全过程地看到来自太阳的日冕物质抛射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Location, location, location. We see CMEs all the time from the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.68,0:28:04.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在中心旋转时大量的物质抛射从太阳的背后转出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A lot of them, as the center is rotated around, are from the backside of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.55,0:28:09.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由于不会面对地球 所以很少关注\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That would not be face towards the Earth, so that would be less of a concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.39,0:28:15.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着太阳的旋转 那个活动的区域逐渐靠近中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the Sun rotates around and that active region gets more into the center of the disk,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.29,0:28:19.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对我们来说那是我们要关注的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}looking at us, then that's when we would be concerned with.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.32,0:28:24.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着它的自转太阳的中心如同杀伤区\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From the center of the Sun, as it rotates around, is the kill zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.80,0:28:36.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着黑子旋转开始直接面对地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the sunspot rotates around and begins to face directly at Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.38,0:28:39.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,此时我们开始被风暴困扰了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's when we really have to worry about a storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.11,0:28:41.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果此时风暴停止\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If a big storm leaves off then,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.75,0:28:46.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会直接瞄准地球 风暴的全部的影响力会冲击地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it can aim directly at Earth, and the full force of the storm slams into the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.27,0:28:54.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像猎枪瞄准靶子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's like a shotgun aiming at a target.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.24,0:28:58.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,射击造成许多死亡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The more dead on the shot,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.25,0:29:02.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将可能会造成严重的损害\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the more likely serious damage will be inflicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.97,0:29:14.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,巨大的威胁还来自惊人的美景\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With great danger also comes astonishing beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.57,0:29:20.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳风暴会产生宏伟的行星的光表演\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Solar storms generate majestic planetary lightshows.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.49,0:29:24.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,五彩缤纷的微光幕帘叫做极光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The shimmering courtains of colour called the Aurora.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.23,0:29:32.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,极光就像霓虹灯活动在巨大的空中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Auroras work like neon signs, on an enormous scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.55,0:29:39.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在霓虹灯里电流引导带电粒子进入充满气体的管子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In a neon sign, electricity introduces charged particles into a gas-filled tube.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.41,0:29:42.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,气体里的粒子跳跃起来 开始发光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The particles in the gas are excited and start to glow.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.00,0:29:46.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果管子里只有氖气 就发红光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If the tube has only neon inside, it will glow red.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.83,0:29:51.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,放进其它气体如氩 就会产生完整的色谱带\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By adding other gases, like argon, a whole range of colors can be produced.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.10,0:29:56.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,霓虹灯是靠管子里的电流驱动的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The neon sign is driven by the electric field inside the tube,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.00,0:30:02.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而极光的驱动是靠磁场和来自太阳的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whereas the Auroras are actually driven by the magnetic field and energy from the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.36,0:30:06.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由于太阳风暴里活跃的粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the energetic particles in a solar storm
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.17,0:30:09.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沿着地球的磁场流入两极\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}stream along Earth's magnetic field towards the Poles,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.69,0:30:14.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,激发大气里的元素使其发光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they excite elements in our atmosphere causing them to glow.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.11,0:30:25.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,氧分子发出绿或红色\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Oxygen molecules emit a green or red color.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.59,0:30:29.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,氮分子发出粉色 兰色和紫色\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And nytrogen emits pinks, blues and violets.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.47,0:30:34.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然这些恐怖的光通常被限定在两极\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}While these ghostly lights are usually confined to the Poles,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.59,0:30:38.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,极端强烈的太阳风暴也会驱使它们靠近赤道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}extremely strong solar storms can drive them closer to the Equator.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.28,0:30:44.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,1859年一个巨大的太阳耀斑引发的磁暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1859 a geomagnetic storm ignited by a huge solar flare
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.41,0:30:47.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在远在罗马这样的南方制造了极光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}created Auroras as far south as Rome.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.09,0:30:51.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,1859年的风暴是一个罕见的大事件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The 1859 storm was an unusually powerful event
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.65,0:30:55.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被称为"完美太阳风暴"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that some have called "the perfect solar storm"
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.37,0:30:59.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,1859年的风暴告诉了我们一点点太阳的所作所为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The 1859 storm taught us a little something about what the Sun can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.18,0:31:03.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,风暴是如此的激烈 组合是如此的完美\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The storm was so intense and the alignment was so perfect,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.58,0:31:06.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球的天然屏障简直不堪一击\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that it simply overwhelmed Earth's natural defenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.91,0:31:15.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个巨大的太阳耀斑在太阳上喷发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A huge solar flare erupts on the surface of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.85,0:31:20.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,9300万英哩的路程才不到一天\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Less than a day later and 93 million miles away,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.65,0:31:25.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,横跨地球的通讯线缆开始爆出火花\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the wires the carry communications across the Earth, begin to spark.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.37,0:31:27.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,折磨着全世界\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Business grinds to a halt worldwide
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.97,0:31:31.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当野火被小小的闪光点燃时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as wild fires are ignited by the smoldering lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.01,0:31:37.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在同一时刻五颜六色的极光照亮了遍布全球的城市\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the same time, colorful Auroras light up the skies of cities around the globe.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.28,0:31:43.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球正好被完美太阳风暴造访\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth has just been visited by the perfect solar storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.53,0:31:47.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳激起这难以置信的耀斑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun kicked up this just incredible solar flare
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.35,0:31:50.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大量能量冲向地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and a massive amount of energy headed towards Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.44,0:31:55.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个风暴不仅是两个有记录的 不仅是最大的一个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Not only was this storm one of the two most powerul on record,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.06,0:31:57.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且还是最快的一个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it was also one of the fastest.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.14,0:32:03.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑子的喷射很快到达地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ejecting from a sunspot aimed directly at Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.65,0:32:08.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它快速地从太阳到地球还不到18小时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it raced from the Sun to our planet in less than 18 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.11,0:32:16.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如今用最快的宇宙飞船到太阳也要化几年功夫\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, it takes a really fast rocketship years to get to the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.09,0:32:19.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个风暴--带电粒子团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This storm, this cloud of electrified particles,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.90,0:32:22.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到达这里不到一天时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}managed to get here in less than a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.27,0:32:23.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,快得难以置信\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's incredibly fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.04,0:32:30.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,幸运的是完美太阳风暴发生在1859年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Fortunately, the perfect solar storm took place in 1859,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.00,0:32:35.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当时受攻击的地球上的科技还只是电报\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when the only technology vulnerable to the onslaught was the telegraph.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.53,0:32:40.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,自从进入了高科技时代\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Since the era in wich we've become dependant on high technology,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.75,0:32:44.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们等着看另一个完美太阳风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we've yet to see another perfect solar storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.63,0:32:48.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,问题是它还会发生吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The question remains: Could it happen again?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.44,0:32:52.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,若是发生了一个像那个的风暴？会有另一个完美风暴吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What if we have another one like that? Can we have another perfect storm?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.28,0:32:55.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我说会的 无须质疑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I'd say yes we can, there's no doubt about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.83,0:33:03.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,今天 对我们的影响 相比较1859年可能 毁灭性的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The effects that would be on us today compared to 1859 could be devastating.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.94,0:33:12.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对地球的 对通讯的影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The effects on Earth and on our communication systems,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.48,0:33:15.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们并不确切知道 那是惊心动魄的一部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we don't exactly know. That's the scary part.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.95,0:33:19.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有可能我们的现代技术遭到打击\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's likely that our modern technologies would be battered
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.38,0:33:22.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像海边的狂风中的房屋一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like beachfront houses during a hurricane.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.06,0:33:30.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想像一下如果我们失去了移动电话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Imagine if we lost all the satellites that relay cellphone calls,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.35,0:33:33.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,电视信号和银行传递依赖的卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}television signals and bank transactions.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.17,0:33:34.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果发生在同一时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And what if at the same time,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.80,0:33:40.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,电力供应的故障一连串的雪崩 把所有地方带进黑暗几个小时或几个星期\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the failure of power grids cascaded whole regions into darkness for hours, or weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.34,0:33:45.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果这些基本服务不能很快恢复\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If these essential services couldn't be restored quickly,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.80,0:33:48.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将会造成混乱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}chaos wouldn't be far behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.70,0:33:54.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会给社会 给生活在地球上的男女老少\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It would definitely be a ripple effect upon society
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.41,0:33:57.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,带来可怕的后果\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and every man and woman and child that lives on this Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.87,0:34:02.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳风暴像飓风那样难以预报\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Solar storms can be as hard to predict as hurricanes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.04,0:34:07.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当下一个完美风暴来临时 预报员缺少预报技术\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}While forecasters lack the technology to foretell the next pefect storm,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.46,0:34:10.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们知道打击终将到来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they do know that one would be more likely to hit
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.26,0:34:14.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在匆匆看过太阳11年的黑子周期后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at the peek of the Sun's eleven-year sunspot cycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.56,0:34:18.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳每11年磁场的方向变化后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What happens is the Sun reverses the direction of its magnetic field
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.64,0:34:19.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会发生什么？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}every eleven years.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.87,0:34:23.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以在22年里它总是变过去 回过来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So in 22 years it reverses and comes back to where it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.49,0:34:26.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当我们接近每11年的逆转时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As we near the reversal every eleven years,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.43,0:34:31.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑子的数量增加 太阳活动达到峰值\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the number of sunspots increases and there's a spike in solar activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.40,0:34:33.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们称那周期为"太阳活动最大期"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We call that period solar maximum
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.53,0:34:37.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而那些是5年分布周期\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and those periods are interspersed about 5 years apart
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.31,0:34:39.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是从太阳活动最大期里分离出来的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from periods we call solar minimum.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.90,0:34:43.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以这11年太阳来回折腾\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So you have this eleven year back and forth
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.25,0:34:45.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有时非常惊人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}between the Sun being sometimes very ferocious,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.97,0:34:49.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,变得疯狂 一直就像独立日的烟火\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it goes crazy and it's like the 4th of July with fireworks all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.00,0:34:51.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,接着开始缓慢停止\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then it starts to ramp down
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.49,0:34:54.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几年后会安静下来直到变成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and for a few years it gets quieter until we get to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.07,0:34:58.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个小点 像个灿烂过的爆竹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a low point where there is a firecracker now and then but not a lot going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.43,0:35:03.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像飓风季节 太阳活动最大期在强度上会变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just like hurricane seasons, solar maximums vary in intensity.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.33,0:35:07.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳会产生比其它时候更强的风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some produce many more powerful storms than others.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.37,0:35:11.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管在一般的太阳活动最小期 科学家也要小心地观察它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Although we're currently at solar minimum, scientists are watching carefully
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.62,0:35:15.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,留意下一次最大的太阳能可能释放的时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to see what mayhem the next solar max might unleash.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.45,0:35:18.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最近的一次太阳活动最大期大约在2001年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The last solar maximum was in about 2001
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.12,0:35:22.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以下一次可能在2012年 但预报也会不一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and so the next one ought to be about 2012, but there are different predictions.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.11,0:35:25.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,整个太阳物理学家焦急地等待着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The whole field of solar physicists is basically waiting with bated breath
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.56,0:35:27.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将要实际发生的情况\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to see what actually happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.35,0:35:30.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们对将要发生的事情有一些大的分歧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are some wildly divergent opinions on what's gonna happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.86,0:35:34.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,某个团队认为下一个太阳周期\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One group is suggesting that this next solar cycle
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.42,0:35:37.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会是现代最强的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could be the strongest in modern times.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.21,0:35:45.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果那些预报准确的话地球将走上疯狂之路\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If those predictions are correct, Earth could be in for a wild ride.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.86,0:35:49.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们将不得不重复1859年的痛苦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We might have to worry about a repeat of the 1859 event.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.78,0:35:52.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果今天发生的话将造成深重的灾难\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If that would happen today it would wreak untold damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.69,0:35:55.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在和平时期里 我们需要认识许多关于太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're gonna learn a whole lot about what can happen
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.45,0:35:58.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对现代科技产生的影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to modern technology when the Sun bows its top.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.82,0:36:02.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳喷发的众多暴行发生在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Much of the violence in the Sun erupts here,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.70,0:36:06.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地狱般的 外部大气层中的日冕里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the hellish outer atmosphere known as the corona.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.04,0:36:10.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个区域长期以来就是太阳的一大秘密\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This region has long held one of the great solar mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.99,0:36:15.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为即使距太阳高热核心有50万英哩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because even though it's half a million miles from the heat-generating core,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.64,0:36:18.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还是有数百万度的高温\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it burns at millions of degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.58,0:36:21.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这似乎违背物理定律\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This seems to violate the very laws of physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.33,0:36:24.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那非常奇怪 这里有只温度计\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's very strange. I have a thermometer here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.87,0:36:27.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果我把温度计靠近火\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If I hold the thermometer close to the fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.86,0:36:29.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有很高的读数\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it reads a very high reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.76,0:36:32.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,探针测出超过200度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Where the probe is right now it's over 200 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.11,0:36:36.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而如果把探针稍微离开点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And if I pull the probe out a little farther from the fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.17,0:36:38.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你瞧 下降了90度左右\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ok, it drops down to about 90 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.26,0:36:42.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,下一步把它伸进中心 温度更低了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, the farther I get from the center, the cooler it gets.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.77,0:36:46.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳大气日冕的温度猛增 同核心一样热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the atmosphere, the corona of the Sun, the temperature soars as hot as the core.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.00,0:36:50.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那犹如 我是说距我背后很远的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's as if, I were to say, well, way off behind me there,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.20,0:36:53.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,火堆里传出的热量和火堆里一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the heat from the fire is as hot as the fire itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.15,0:36:55.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至可以传得更远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}even though it's very far from the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.12,0:36:59.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是什么造成了日冕的高温呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What force could possibly cause the superheating of the corona?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.63,0:37:03.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,答案会让你震惊\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The answer will rock you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.39,0:37:09.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,凶狠的日冕以数百万度的温度呼啸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The hellish solar corona rages at millions of degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.68,0:37:12.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几个世纪以来科学家们很困惑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For centuries scientists have been baffled
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.47,0:37:15.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,怎么距离日心这么远的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how anything so far from the Sun's core
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.26,0:37:17.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,仍然会有这么高的温度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could still burn so hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.26,0:37:22.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最近随着改进的人造卫星发回的太阳表面的近距离观察\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Recently, as improved satellites offered a closer view of the solar surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.03,0:37:25.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,线索开始显现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}clues began to emerge.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.60,0:37:29.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在日冕下面太阳表面简直是个火海\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Below the corona the Sun's surface is literally boiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.51,0:37:33.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,原因是整个太阳表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The reason is that the entire surface of the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.39,0:37:37.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,覆盖着对流单元 热物质从太阳里面出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is covered with convection cells, hot material from the inside of the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.62,0:37:41.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,上升穿越到达表面 发光冷却\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that rises up through, reaches the surface, cools off by glowing,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.72,0:37:44.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发出阳光然后沉下去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}giving off sunlight and then sinks back down.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.07,0:37:48.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,升起的每个泡泡有德克萨斯州那么大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Each bubble of material that comes up is about the size of Texas.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.78,0:37:52.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它散布在表面冷却并在5分钟里下沉下去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It spreads out across the surface, cools off and sinks down in 5 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.10,0:37:56.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以这是一个非常剧烈的过程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, that's a tremendously violent process
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.43,0:37:59.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那发生在 不夸张地 几乎所有地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's happening in, literally, almost a million places
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.36,0:38:03.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,覆盖整个太阳表面 日以继夜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}over the entire surface of the Sun, all the time around the clock, 24/7.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.10,0:38:09.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沸腾不仅仅剧烈而且非常喧闹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This boiling is not only violent, it's also extremely loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.27,0:38:14.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳是非常喧闹的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun is a tremendously loud place.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.47,0:38:20.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,若想像一下 整个太阳表面覆盖的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you could imagine covering the entire surface of the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.00,0:38:25.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,吵闹者 和你曾去光临的摇滚音乐会相比一样的歇斯底里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with speakers being driven as hard as the loudest rock concert you've ever been to,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.57,0:38:30.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳表面就这么闹得慌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that would be comparable to how loud it really is on the surface of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.20,0:38:34.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳表面的搅动甚至会产生声能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun's churning surface creates enough sound energy
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.63,0:38:37.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,给日冕供给数百万度热量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to superheat the corona to millions of degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.65,0:38:42.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家相信这些声波和能量的集合物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists believe that a combination of these sound waves and energy
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.42,0:38:44.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是缘于太阳磁场的作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the Sun's magnetic field
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.17,0:38:48.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是日冕产生极端高温的原因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is responsible for the extreme temperatures found in the corona.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.77,0:38:52.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从地球上观察日冕的唯一机会\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The only time you can actually see the corona from Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.09,0:38:57.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是在太阳系中最耀眼的高潮时刻--\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is at the climax of one of the most dazzling displays in the Solar System,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.73,0:38:59.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-日全食\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a total solar eclipse.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.56,0:39:02.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在科学家搞明白之前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Before scientists understood them,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.66,0:39:06.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些严肃令人振奋的事情只被当成恐惧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}these awe inspiring events instilled only fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.71,0:39:11.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,古代的中国人认为是龙吃掉了太阳\N【非龙也!乃天狗食日!是风趣的比喻 东方敏锐的智慧!】\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The ancient Chinese believed that a dragon was devouring the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.71,0:39:14.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么是日食真的发生了什么？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So what's really happening in a solar eclipse?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.88,0:39:19.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,简单的道理是月亮运转遮住了太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In simplest terms it's when the Moon blocks our view of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.59,0:39:23.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想像一下你非常快乐的在看电影\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Imagine that you're sitting in a movies watching very happily
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.83,0:39:26.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,荧幕上在放映 有人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}something going on on the screen and then somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.64,0:39:29.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在你前面经过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the row in front of you comes across
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.95,0:39:31.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,挡住了你的视线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and blocks your view.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.83,0:39:33.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在电影院里你不希望这种人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In a movie theater you might not want that person
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.87,0:39:35.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,挡在你的前面 然而\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to come across in front of you, but at
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.57,0:39:39.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在日食里我们非常欢迎月亮越过太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an eclipse we're very lucky to have the Moon come across the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.41,0:39:41.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非常希望它正好横过太阳的中间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we're lucky to have it come right across the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.84,0:39:47.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们也非常庆幸 月亮(直径)虽然比太阳(直径)小400倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're also lucky that the Moon, although it's 400 times smaller than the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.38,0:39:50.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但也正好400倍靠近我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is also 400 times closer to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.55,0:39:53.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个宇宙的巧合意味着两个物体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This cosmic coincidence means that the two objects
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.63,0:39:56.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,刚好尺寸大小一样地挂在天空上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just happen to be the same apparent size in our sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.82,0:40:00.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正好一个可以完全遮住另外一个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which allows for one to completely block out the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.93,0:40:04.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个奇妙的宇宙现象只发生在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This magnificent cosmic event only happens
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.72,0:40:08.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,月亮的轨道横穿过地球和太阳之间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when the path of the Moon intersects the line between the Earth and the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.80,0:40:12.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,月亮的轨道有近5度的倾斜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Moon's orbit is tilted slightly about 5 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.22,0:40:15.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果不是的话 每个月都会有日食\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If it wasn't we would have an eclipse every month.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.99,0:40:17.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那时我们会觉得无聊\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then we'd be bored,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.45,0:40:19.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是我们觉得不无聊是因为大部分的月份\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but we're not bored because most months
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.04,0:40:22.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,月亮的轨道在日地之间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Moon goes above or below
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.02,0:40:26.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,的上方或下方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the place where the line goes from the Earth to the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.99,0:40:30.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不是每个月都有一次日全食\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So instead of one every month we get a total eclipse
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.82,0:40:34.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而是地球上的一些地方每1 5年才有一次\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}somewhere on Earth about once every year and a half.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.72,0:40:36.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当月亮挡在太阳前面时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the Moon slides in front of the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.96,0:40:39.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把影子投在地球上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it casts a shadow onto the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.34,0:40:41.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,外面的部分影子是模糊的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The outer part, where the shadow is fainter,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.99,0:40:43.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,称为半影\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is called the penumbra.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.69,0:40:47.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你站在半影扫过的区域里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you're standing within the swath traced by the penumbra,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.55,0:40:49.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当它沿着地球表面移动时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as it moves along the Earth's surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.62,0:40:51.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你就只能看到日偏食\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then you'll see only a partial eclipse.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.49,0:40:57.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而进到里面黑影的部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But travel to a spot within the path of the dark inner shadow,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.86,0:40:59.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,叫做本影\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}called the umbra,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.27,0:41:03.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你将体验到日全食的雄伟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you'll experience the majesty of a total eclipse.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.99,0:41:10.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,假如你无法去日全食发生的地方 还有一个选择\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's another option if you can't travel to the path of totality,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.05,0:41:13.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就在一个地方等足够的时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}wait in one place long enough
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.16,0:41:16.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,日全食会正好在你的头顶上的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and a total eclipse will pass right over your head
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.13,0:41:18.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大约每300年一次\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about once every 300 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.38,0:41:27.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳 我们太阳系的最明亮的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun, that shining star of our Solar System,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.13,0:41:31.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即出奇的美丽 但又是极度的残暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is capable of both astonishing beauty and ferocious violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.09,0:41:35.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,似乎无法使人相信\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It seems impossible to believe,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.49,0:41:37.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它不会永恒生存\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it won't be around forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.66,0:41:43.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最终连太阳也必然灭亡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Eventually even the Sun must die.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.56,0:41:46.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳核的燃料数量是固定的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun has a fixed amount of fuel in its core,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.34,0:41:52.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,经过燃烧其速度是可以计算出来的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it is undergoing fusion at a rate that you can calculate.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.37,0:41:54.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有太阳使用燃料的速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So here's the rate it's using its fuel,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.91,0:41:56.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有多少燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}here's how much fuel you have,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.84,0:42:00.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通过简单的计算就可以表明太阳什么时候会灭亡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so it's a simple calculation to show when the Sun will die,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.23,0:42:03.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大概会在50亿年左右\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that's in about a five billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.03,0:42:06.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是的 可惜太阳不会在大爆炸中走完一生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, unfortunately the Sun will not go out with a bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.65,0:42:09.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它太小了不会像超新星那样喷发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's too small to erupt in a supernova.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.51,0:42:12.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不管怎样太阳会发生特别的情况\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However stars do a peculiar thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.92,0:42:16.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最有可能是随着冷却会趋于白热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they're one of the few things around that get hotter as they cool off.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.09,0:42:20.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着氢燃料的用尽 我们亲密的太阳会变冷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As it exhausts its hydrogen fuel, our nearest star will cool
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.94,0:42:23.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在引力作用下逐渐崩塌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and gradually collapse under the force of gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.97,0:42:27.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,崩塌产生的能量会再次加热日核\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Energy from this collapse will start heating up the core again
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.30,0:42:32.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到数亿度 足够的温度开始使氦核点火\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to hundreds of millions of degrees, hot enough to start burning helium.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.94,0:42:35.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在氦燃烧额外的加热中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Onto the extra heat of the helium burning,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.11,0:42:39.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳将膨胀成巨大的天体 称为红巨星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the star will expand into a monstrous orb called a red giant.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.97,0:42:42.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是如此的庞大会吞没\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It'll get so big it will engulf
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.12,0:42:47.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,整个轨道上的水星 金星和地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the entire orbits of Mercury, Venus and Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.58,0:42:49.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不可能再围绕着它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You don't want to be around for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.89,0:42:52.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你会希望"行星跳跃"轨道以提升安全度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You want to be planet-hopping your way to safety
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.79,0:42:54.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在此发生之前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}long before this happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.75,0:42:59.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在太阳膨胀时地球会稍微改变它的轨道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth is likely to change its orbit slightly as the star expands,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.29,0:43:01.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们不会被吞没\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so that it won't be engulfed.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.26,0:43:04.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是在讨论全球变暖时你不会想到这\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Still, talking about global warming, you wouldn't want to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.08,0:43:08.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳的外层会变得不稳定\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The outer layers of our Sun will eventually become so unstable
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.13,0:43:11.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会飞进太空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that they will fly off into space,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.39,0:43:15.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最后剩下地球般大小的日核\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}leaving behind a small core about the size of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.15,0:43:18.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳的大部分会收缩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So remember we've shrunk most of the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.57,0:43:21.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由一百万英哩直径缩小到像地球(直径7918英哩)\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is a million miles across, to the size of the Earth which is
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.68,0:43:24.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那样6000英哩跨度大小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}more like 6000 miles across.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.75,0:43:29.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们过去伟大的太阳慢慢地冷却为余烬\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our once great star reduced to a slowly cooling cinder.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.76,0:43:32.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球上的生命将寿终正寝\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Life as we know it on Earth will cease to exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.40,0:43:35.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就是太阳的末日\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that is the death of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.76,0:43:40.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所有这些对人类是个厄耗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All of this is bad news for the human race,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.70,0:43:43.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而来看看光明的一面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but look on the bright side.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.28,0:43:47.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们会有50亿年对这个灾难进行补救\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We've got five billion years to prepare for this disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.32,0:43:52.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在人类沐浴在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For now, humanity basks in the glow of a Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.84,0:43:54.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,全盛期的太阳辉光中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the prime of its life.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.11,0:43:58.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家揭去了我们最亲密恒星的许多秘密\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Science has uncovered many of the secrets of our nearest star,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.13,0:44:01.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但我们对这个美人依然要保持着敬畏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but we remain awed by its beauty,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.70,0:44:01.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢观赏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thanks For Viewing
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.74,0:44:05.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且要永远地提防着它的神谴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and ever more wary of its wrath.
